what is dependency injection in java?
A. Dependency Injection is the concept in which objects get other required objects from outside.
   It can be implemented in any programming language.

What is static binding and dynamic binding?
A. Static binding is when the type of object is determined at compile time by the compiler. Dynamic binding is when
   the type is determined at run time. Static binding uses Type information for binding while Dynamic binding uses
   Objects to resolve binding.








